WEBVTT

00:02.711 --> 00:04.212
[ THUDDING ]

00:04.254 --> 00:06.214
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

00:06.256 --> 00:08.258
[ HARDISON GRUNTING ]

00:13.681 --> 00:16.183
Wakey, wakey.

00:17.935 --> 00:19.394
WHERE AM I?

00:19.436 --> 00:21.939
Well, see for yourself.

00:35.744 --> 00:39.414
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

00:39.456 --> 00:41.709
[ THUDDING ]

00:43.752 --> 00:46.171
[ GRUNTS ]

00:46.213 --> 00:49.675
NO. NO.

00:49.717 --> 00:52.219
N-O-O-O-O-O!

01:00.227 --> 01:03.104
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

01:05.440 --> 01:08.527
[ ORGAN MUSIC PLAYS ]

01:08.569 --> 01:10.278
OUR FATHER TRUSTED YOU!

01:10.320 --> 01:12.531
PLEASE, LOWER YOUR VOICES.

01:12.573 --> 01:16.368
YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY PEOPLE HERE

01:12.573 --> 01:16.368
WHO'VE LOST SOMEONE THEY LOVED.

01:16.410 --> 01:18.704
HE GAVE YOU EVERYTHING HE HAD,

01:16.410 --> 01:18.704
AND YOU STOLE IT.

01:18.746 --> 01:19.830
WE'RE GOING TO THE POLICE.

01:19.872 --> 01:22.082
LET'S JUST DISCUSS THIS

01:19.872 --> 01:22.082
IN MY OFFICE.

01:22.123 --> 01:23.375
I'M SURE WE CAN

01:22.123 --> 01:23.375
RESOLVE EVERYTHING.

01:23.417 --> 01:24.752
PLEASE, JUST -- JUST FOLLOW ME.

01:28.129 --> 01:30.257
MOTHER...

01:30.298 --> 01:31.717
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

01:31.759 --> 01:33.552
GIDEON, EMERY, DEAREST,

01:33.594 --> 01:36.597
THERE SEEMS TO BE SOME CONFUSION

01:33.594 --> 01:36.597
WITH THIS CONTRACT.

01:36.638 --> 01:38.223
WOULD YOU PLEASE

01:36.638 --> 01:38.223
STRAIGHTEN THINGS OUT?

01:40.851 --> 01:43.144
I WANT TO SEE

01:40.851 --> 01:43.144
MY FATHER'S PAPERWORK.

01:43.186 --> 01:44.563
OF COURSE, MR. NEWTON.

01:45.146 --> 01:46.648
-OHH!

01:45.146 --> 01:46.648
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

01:46.690 --> 01:48.191
[ GASPING ]

01:48.233 --> 01:49.610
WALK AWAY.

01:49.651 --> 01:50.778
[ GROANS, COUGHS ]

01:50.819 --> 01:52.821
-STOP IT!

01:50.819 --> 01:52.821
-FORGET ABOUT THE MONEY.

01:52.863 --> 01:55.407
IF WE SEE YOU TWO HERE AGAIN,

01:55.449 --> 01:58.118
YOU'LL WISH

01:55.449 --> 01:58.118
WE LET YOU OFF THIS EASY.

02:00.454 --> 02:05.417
MY FATHER DIED LAST MONTH --

02:00.454 --> 02:05.417
PANCREATIC CANCER.

02:05.459 --> 02:07.252
THEY FOUND IT

02:05.459 --> 02:07.252
AT STAGE FOUR, SO...

02:07.294 --> 02:08.587
I'M SORRY.

02:08.629 --> 02:10.547
AT LEAST WE KNOW

02:08.629 --> 02:10.547
HE'S AT PEACE NOW.

02:10.589 --> 02:12.049
POP WANTED TO MAKE SURE

02:12.091 --> 02:14.426
THAT MY BROTHER AND I WERE

02:12.091 --> 02:14.426
TAKEN CARE OF AFTER HE WAS GONE,

02:14.468 --> 02:18.097
SO HE MADE HIS FUNERAL

02:14.468 --> 02:18.097
ARRANGEMENTS IN ADVANCE

02:18.138 --> 02:19.807
WITH DARLENE WICKETT.

02:19.848 --> 02:21.475
HE GAVE HER $15,000.

02:21.516 --> 02:24.311
THE FUNERAL BUSINESS

02:21.516 --> 02:24.311
IS VERY EXPENSIVE.

02:24.352 --> 02:26.063
BUT AFTER MY FATHER DIED,

02:26.105 --> 02:28.774
DARLENE TOLD US THAT

02:26.105 --> 02:28.774
SHE HAD NO RECORD OF THE MONEY,

02:28.816 --> 02:30.985
THAT SHE'D NEVER EVEN

02:28.816 --> 02:30.985
HEARD OF MY FATHER.

02:31.026 --> 02:33.320
SO IT'S A BREACH OF CONTRACT.

02:33.361 --> 02:34.822
THERE  IS  NO CONTRACT, MR. FORD.

02:34.863 --> 02:36.197
WHAT DO YOU MEAN

02:34.863 --> 02:36.197
THERE'S NO CONTRACT?

02:36.239 --> 02:37.783
POP WAS IN THE MIDDLE OF CHEMO

02:36.239 --> 02:37.783
WHEN HE MET DARLENE.

02:37.825 --> 02:39.576
SHE TOOK ADVANTAGE

02:37.825 --> 02:39.576
OF HIS ILLNESS.

02:39.618 --> 02:41.411
AND WE CAN'T AFFORD

02:39.618 --> 02:41.411
TO HIRE A LAWYER.

02:41.453 --> 02:45.165
WE HAD TO RUN OUR CREDIT CARDS

02:41.453 --> 02:45.165
UP AT ANOTHER FUNERAL HOME

02:41.453 --> 02:45.165
TO BURY POP.

02:45.206 --> 02:47.042
OKAY, LISTEN, I AM GONNA

02:45.206 --> 02:47.042
DO EVERYTHING I CAN

02:47.084 --> 02:48.502
TO GET

02:47.084 --> 02:48.502
YOUR FATHER'S MONEY BACK.

02:48.543 --> 02:52.006
THANK YOU, MR. FORD,

02:48.543 --> 02:52.006
BUT IT'S NOT ABOUT THE MONEY.

02:52.047 --> 02:56.844
THIS WAS POP'S FINAL GIFT.

02:52.047 --> 02:56.844
HE WANTED TO PROTECT US.

02:56.885 --> 02:59.178
DARLENE TOOK THAT AWAY.

03:03.558 --> 03:06.227
PARKER, WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

03:08.271 --> 03:11.025
HOW DOES SHE KNOW THAT, NATE --

03:11.066 --> 03:14.695
THAT HER FATHER'S AT PEACE?

03:14.736 --> 03:17.572
[ SIGHS ]

03:22.703 --> 03:24.705
FAITH.

03:27.082 --> 03:29.250
FAITH, PARKER.

03:34.715 --> 03:37.551
THE RICH AND POWERFUL

03:34.715 --> 03:37.551
TAKE WHAT THEY WANT.

03:37.592 --> 03:39.469
WE STEAL IT BACK FOR YOU.

03:45.893 --> 03:50.480
SOMETIMES, BAD GUYS

03:45.893 --> 03:50.480
MAKE THE BEST GOOD GUYS.

03:52.149 --> 03:53.483
WE PROVIDE...

03:54.735 --> 03:56.737
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

04:06.830 --> 04:08.957
WHAT'S UP WITH PARKER?

04:08.999 --> 04:10.792
IT'S PARKER.

04:10.834 --> 04:12.460
YOU'RE GONNA LOVE THIS.

04:12.502 --> 04:14.462
DARLENE WICKETT AND HER SONS

04:14.504 --> 04:17.507
ARE EMBEZZLING MONEY FROM

04:14.504 --> 04:17.507
THE DYING AND THE GRIEVING.

04:17.549 --> 04:19.051
IT'S THE OLDEST GRIFT

04:17.549 --> 04:19.051
IN THE BOOK.

04:19.093 --> 04:21.553
AND THE CRUELEST. EVEN I NEVER

04:19.093 --> 04:21.553
RAN THAT ONE -- IT'S TACKY.

04:21.595 --> 04:23.680
NOW, THE WICKETTS HAVE OPERATED

04:21.595 --> 04:23.680
ALL OVER THE COUNTRY.

04:23.722 --> 04:25.182
OUR RECORDS SHOW

04:23.722 --> 04:25.182
FUNERAL LICENSES

04:25.224 --> 04:27.601
FROM THREE DIFFERENT STATES,

04:25.224 --> 04:27.601
BUT FOR THE LAST FIVE YEARS,

04:27.642 --> 04:29.603
THEY'VE BEEN HERE

04:27.642 --> 04:29.603
IN MASSACHUSETTS.

04:29.644 --> 04:31.772
WHY HAS NO ONE REPORTED THEM

04:29.644 --> 04:31.772
TO THE POLICE?

04:31.813 --> 04:34.608
WELL, THEY HAVE, BUT, UH,

04:31.813 --> 04:34.608
SHE HAS BULLETPROOF ALIASES

04:34.649 --> 04:36.568
FOR ALL THE STATES

04:34.649 --> 04:36.568
SHE'S WORKED IN.

04:36.610 --> 04:38.070
NOW, THE RECORDS THAT WE FOUND

04:38.112 --> 04:42.741
SHOW THAT THE WICKETTS

04:38.112 --> 04:42.741
HAVE STOLEN $500,000.

04:42.783 --> 04:44.243
-WHERE'S THE MONEY?

04:42.783 --> 04:44.243
-WELL, IT'S NOT IN ANY BANK.

04:44.284 --> 04:45.577
CREDIT-CARD RECORDS SHOW

04:45.619 --> 04:47.829
THAT SHE HAS RECENTLY

04:45.619 --> 04:47.829
BOUGHT A WALL SAFE,

04:47.871 --> 04:50.832
WHICH IS THIS RIGHT HERE.

04:50.874 --> 04:52.126
OH.

04:52.167 --> 04:56.797
OOH, MURPHY-BEYER,

04:52.167 --> 04:56.797
MODEL PRK-11-21.

04:56.838 --> 04:58.132
NICE.

04:58.173 --> 05:00.425
OKAY, SHE'S A HORRIBLE

04:58.173 --> 05:00.425
HUMAN BEING,

05:00.467 --> 05:02.427
BUT SHE'S GOT SOLID TASTE

05:00.467 --> 05:02.427
IN HOME SECURITY.

05:02.469 --> 05:03.678
[ DOOR OPENS, HARDISON SIGHS ]

05:03.720 --> 05:05.346
THESE DUST MITES ARE

05:03.720 --> 05:05.346
JUST GONNA EAT ME ALIVE.

05:05.388 --> 05:06.974
THAT'S THE BLUEPRINTS

05:05.388 --> 05:06.974
FROM TOWN HALL...

05:07.015 --> 05:09.101
AND THE LAST TIME I GO INTO

05:07.015 --> 05:09.101
A BASEMENT WITH THIS GUY.

05:11.019 --> 05:13.772
I ALREADY GOT THE PHOTOS

05:11.019 --> 05:13.772
OVER HERE.

05:13.814 --> 05:17.776
THAT'S THE WICKETT FUNERAL HOME.

05:13.814 --> 05:17.776
IT'S A TWO-STORY HOUSE.

05:17.818 --> 05:19.945
YOU GOT YOUR EMBALMING ROOM

05:17.818 --> 05:19.945
IN THE BASEMENT.

05:19.987 --> 05:21.696
YOU GOT YOUR

05:19.987 --> 05:21.696
VIEWING CHAMBERS AND YOUR OFFICE

05:21.738 --> 05:23.657
ON THE FIRST FLOOR.

05:23.698 --> 05:25.784
AND BINGO -- PRIVATE

05:23.698 --> 05:25.784
LIVING QUARTERS ON THE SECOND.

05:25.826 --> 05:27.828
THEY LIVE AND WORK THERE.

05:27.869 --> 05:29.955
OKAY. SO, FUNERAL HOMES

05:27.869 --> 05:29.955
ARE BUSIEST ON THE WEEKENDS.

05:29.997 --> 05:33.167
IT'S THE EASIEST TIME TO KIND OF

05:29.997 --> 05:33.167
BLEND IN WITH THE MOURNERS.

05:33.208 --> 05:35.294
UM...I'M SORRY.

05:33.208 --> 05:35.294
WHAT, NATE?

05:35.335 --> 05:38.588
OKAY, GUYS, WE ARE GONNA

05:35.335 --> 05:38.588
GO STEAL A FUNERAL.

05:44.052 --> 05:46.013
OOH.

05:46.054 --> 05:49.683
THERE SHE IS,

05:46.054 --> 05:49.683
THE PERFECT HOSTESS.

05:49.724 --> 05:52.060
RIGHT ON SCHEDULE.

05:49.724 --> 05:52.060
HARDISON, HEADING YOUR WAY.

05:52.102 --> 05:55.730
SOPHIE, I HATE IT WHEN YOU MAKE

05:52.102 --> 05:55.730
ME WEAR THESE DANG CUFFLINKS.

05:55.772 --> 05:57.191
Hardison, everybody owns

05:55.772 --> 05:57.191
a good suit,

05:57.232 --> 05:59.358
BUT ONLY THE RICH

05:57.232 --> 05:59.358
OWN A GOOD PAIR OF CUFFLINKS.

05:59.400 --> 06:01.736
DARLENE IS GONNA KNOW THAT.

06:04.072 --> 06:06.365
OH.

06:06.407 --> 06:09.368
YOU MUST BE MR. DELACROIX.

06:09.410 --> 06:11.872
I'M DARLENE WICKETT.

06:09.410 --> 06:11.872
THANK YOU FOR WAITING.

06:11.913 --> 06:13.540
I'M -- I'M SO SORRY

06:11.913 --> 06:13.540
FOR YOUR LOSS.

06:13.581 --> 06:15.583
THANK YOU.

06:13.581 --> 06:15.583
THANK YOU, MS. WICKETT.

06:15.625 --> 06:18.962
-MY GREAT AUNTIE -- SHE, UH --

06:15.625 --> 06:18.962
SHE PASSED LAST EVENING.

06:15.625 --> 06:18.962
-MM.

06:19.004 --> 06:22.174
AND THERE ARE SOME STAFF --

06:19.004 --> 06:22.174
THEY SPOKE VERY HIGHLY OF YOU.

06:22.216 --> 06:25.384
NOW, I MUST ADMIT I'M...

06:25.426 --> 06:27.554
I'M A BIT LOST.

06:27.595 --> 06:29.931
OH, MR. DELACROIX.

06:31.683 --> 06:35.979
LET US HELP YOU SAY GOODBYE.

06:37.564 --> 06:42.443
YOU FOCUS ON HEALING

06:37.564 --> 06:42.443
DURING THIS DIFFICULT TIME,

06:42.485 --> 06:44.529
AND MY SONS AND I CAN TAKE CARE

06:42.485 --> 06:44.529
OF EVERYTHING ELSE.

06:53.914 --> 06:56.541
[ SHUDDERS ]

06:56.583 --> 06:59.044
CHILLY.

07:04.799 --> 07:07.177
PARKER, ANYTHING

07:04.799 --> 07:07.177
ON THE METAL DETECTOR?

07:07.219 --> 07:09.554
Three floors, one wall safe --

07:09.596 --> 07:11.723
SOUNDS LIKE A CHALLENGE TO ME.

07:11.765 --> 07:12.891
[ BEEP ]

07:12.933 --> 07:15.518
[ ELECTRONIC PINGING ]

07:18.939 --> 07:21.733
[ SIGHS ]

07:21.775 --> 07:23.902
[ HUMMING ]

07:23.944 --> 07:25.612
[ SIGHS ]

07:25.653 --> 07:26.947
[ SQUISHES ]

07:26.988 --> 07:28.323
EW!

07:30.325 --> 07:32.452
JUST STEPPED

07:30.325 --> 07:32.452
IN SOMETHING SQUISHY.

07:32.493 --> 07:34.621
[ GAGS ]

07:34.662 --> 07:37.332
HOW COME I HAD TO GO

07:34.662 --> 07:37.332
TO THE EMBALMING ROOM, ANYWAY?

07:37.374 --> 07:40.835
IT'S 'CAUSE HARDISON'S TOO

07:37.374 --> 07:40.835
SCARED TO GET IN THE BODY BAG.

07:40.877 --> 07:44.672
Hey, claustrophobia

07:40.877 --> 07:44.672
is a very serious condition.

07:44.714 --> 07:47.259
I got a note from my doctor.

07:44.714 --> 07:47.259
You want to see it?

07:47.301 --> 07:48.969
ELIOT, WHERE ARE YOU?

07:49.010 --> 07:50.220
[ BEEP ]

07:50.262 --> 07:52.472
I'M FASHIONABLY LATE

07:50.262 --> 07:52.472
TO AN EX-CON'S FUNERAL.

07:52.513 --> 07:55.350
I'M GONNA CHECK THE ROOM

07:52.513 --> 07:55.350
FOR A SAFE.

07:55.392 --> 07:57.018
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

07:57.060 --> 07:58.519
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

08:00.981 --> 08:03.817
IT'S NOT EX-CONS -- IT'S COPS.

08:03.858 --> 08:05.819
IT'S A LOTS OF COPS.

08:10.698 --> 08:11.992
HARDISON.

08:12.033 --> 08:16.496
I-I-I GUESS THEY MUST HAVE

08:12.033 --> 08:16.496
SWITCHED THE SCHEDULE.

08:16.537 --> 08:18.457
You guess?

08:18.498 --> 08:21.209
[ Boston accent ]

08:18.498 --> 08:21.209
I GOT CAUGHT UP AT THE, UH,

08:18.498 --> 08:21.209
DRUG STING DOWN IN DORCHESTER,

08:21.251 --> 08:23.878
AND I WASN'T ABLE TO

08:21.251 --> 08:23.878
GET HOME AND CHANGE CLOTHES.

08:23.920 --> 08:25.630
[ SIGHS ]

08:27.299 --> 08:28.758
HEY. THANKS, MAN.

08:28.800 --> 08:30.302
YEAH.

08:31.886 --> 08:33.221
[ LID UNSCREWS ]

08:33.263 --> 08:34.473
HARDISON, WHEN I SEE YOU,

08:33.263 --> 08:34.473
I'M GONNA HIT YOU SO HARD,

08:34.514 --> 08:35.515
YOUR ANCESTORS HURT.

08:35.556 --> 08:38.185
WE HAVE SOMETHING

08:35.556 --> 08:38.185
FOR EVERYONE HERE,

08:38.226 --> 08:43.231
BUT I BELIEVE I HAVE

08:38.226 --> 08:43.231
JUST THE CASKET FOR YOU.

08:49.612 --> 08:52.073
THIS IS THE ADMIRAL --

08:52.115 --> 08:55.243
SOLID-PLANKED CHERRYWOOD

08:55.285 --> 08:59.706
WITH A HAND-POLISH FINISH...

08:59.747 --> 09:04.794
IMPERIAL SATIN, TUXEDO FOLD

08:59.747 --> 09:04.794
WITH MATCHING PILLOW.

09:04.836 --> 09:06.171
HERE.

09:06.213 --> 09:07.381
HMM?

09:07.422 --> 09:09.549
-HERE. HERE.

09:07.422 --> 09:09.549
-NO, I'M --

09:09.590 --> 09:15.055
YEAH. JUST...FEEL HOW SOFT.

09:15.096 --> 09:17.598
-I TOUCHED IT.

09:15.096 --> 09:17.598
-THIS IS MY FAVORITE PART.

09:20.601 --> 09:23.730
A KEEPSAKE NOOK

09:23.771 --> 09:27.567
FOR LETTERS AND MEMENTOS

09:27.608 --> 09:33.365
TO JOURNEY WITH YOUR LOVED ONE

09:27.608 --> 09:33.365
TO THEIR FINAL RESTING PLACE.

09:33.407 --> 09:34.533
IT'S VERY EXQUISITE.

09:34.574 --> 09:36.576
IT'S VERY --

09:34.574 --> 09:36.576
VERY NICE, VERY FINAL.

09:36.617 --> 09:42.290
THIS IS THE EXACT MODEL

09:36.617 --> 09:42.290
I BURIED MY OWN MOTHER IN.

09:43.833 --> 09:46.627
TRULY OUR FINEST CASKET.

09:46.669 --> 09:48.255
NICE TOUCH ABOUT HER MOTHER.

09:48.296 --> 09:49.881
YEAH, ISN'T IT?

09:49.923 --> 09:52.175
ESPECIALLY SINCE THE OLD DEAR

09:49.923 --> 09:52.175
IS ALIVE AND KICKING IN DALLAS.

09:52.217 --> 09:53.218
HMM.

09:58.890 --> 10:01.309
TART.

10:01.351 --> 10:04.104
AWW, HE SEEMED SWEET --

10:01.351 --> 10:04.104
DESERVED BETTER.

10:04.145 --> 10:06.147
PARKER, ELIOT,

10:04.145 --> 10:06.147
YOU FIND ANYTHING?

10:06.189 --> 10:07.648
[ ELECTRONIC PINGING ]

10:07.690 --> 10:12.112
ZIP, ZERO, NIL, NADA --

10:07.690 --> 10:12.112
NOTHING.

10:12.153 --> 10:15.656
THIS ROOM'S CLEAR.

10:12.153 --> 10:15.656
I GOT NOTHING.

10:15.698 --> 10:17.451
GRIFTERS KEEP THEIR CASH CLOSE.

10:17.492 --> 10:19.827
PARKER, CHECK OUT

10:17.492 --> 10:19.827
DARLENE'S BEDROOM UPSTAIRS.

10:19.869 --> 10:22.830
THERE'S ONLY ONE STAIRCASE

10:19.869 --> 10:22.830
THAT LEADS TO THE TOP FLOOR,

10:22.872 --> 10:24.832
AND THE NO-NECK BROTHERS

10:22.872 --> 10:24.832
ARE BLOCKING THE WAY.

10:24.874 --> 10:27.168
PARKER, I DON'T KNOW HOW

10:24.874 --> 10:27.168
YOU'RE GONNA END UP GETTING --

10:27.210 --> 10:30.004
GIDEON, EMERY, IT'S FEELING

10:27.210 --> 10:30.004
A LITTLE WARM IN HERE.

10:30.046 --> 10:31.798
COULD YOU GO DOWN

10:30.046 --> 10:31.798
IN THE BASEMENT

10:31.839 --> 10:33.800
AND FIDDLE

10:31.839 --> 10:33.800
WITH THE AIR CONDITIONER?

10:33.841 --> 10:35.051
HEY, EXCUSE ME?

10:35.093 --> 10:36.428
THERE'S A BUNCH OF KIDS OUTSIDE,

10:35.093 --> 10:36.428
TAGGING CARS.

10:36.470 --> 10:37.554
YOU SHOULD GO, BUT YOU SHOULD --

10:36.470 --> 10:37.554
YOU SHOULD BRING --

10:37.596 --> 10:39.222
BRING YOUR FRIEND WITH YOU.

10:39.264 --> 10:40.974
PARKER, GET OUT OF THERE NOW.

10:41.015 --> 10:43.310
PARKER, ARE YOU CLEAR?

10:43.351 --> 10:44.311
Parker?

10:44.352 --> 10:46.020
A LITTLE BUSY HERE, NATE.

10:49.107 --> 10:52.693
I DIDN'T HAVE TIME

10:49.107 --> 10:52.693
TO GRAB MY GEAR.

10:54.112 --> 10:56.156
OHH!

10:56.197 --> 10:57.449
[ GRUNTS ]

10:57.491 --> 10:59.993
BLOODY HELL!

11:00.034 --> 11:01.995
WELL, WHAT -- WHAT ARE

11:00.034 --> 11:01.995
YOU ALL LOOKING AT?

11:02.036 --> 11:03.204
-D-DON'T LOOK AT HER LIKE THAT.

11:02.036 --> 11:03.204
-[ CRYING ]

11:03.246 --> 11:05.039
I THINK WE'RE ALL

11:03.246 --> 11:05.039
THINKING THE SAME THING --

11:05.081 --> 11:06.916
"BLOODY HELL,

11:05.081 --> 11:06.916
WHY DID HE HAVE TO DIE?!"

11:06.958 --> 11:08.668
MOVE, PARKER. MOVE.

11:08.709 --> 11:11.338
BUT, YOU KNOW, THE --

11:08.709 --> 11:11.338
THE FACT IS HE -- HE DID.

11:11.379 --> 11:12.797
AND -- AND DO YOU KNOW WHAT,

11:11.379 --> 11:12.797
I'M SURE THERE ARE SOME

11:12.839 --> 11:14.007
VERY VALUABLE LESSONS THAT

11:12.839 --> 11:14.007
WE CAN LEARN FROM HIS LIFE.

11:14.048 --> 11:16.343
[ SOBBING ]

11:16.384 --> 11:19.179
OUR COUSIN --

11:16.384 --> 11:19.179
HE TAUGHT ME THE VALUE OF...

11:19.220 --> 11:21.264
-IT'S OKAY.

11:19.220 --> 11:21.264
-...HARD WORK.

11:21.306 --> 11:23.682
WOW, AND HE -- AND HE TAUGHT ME

11:21.306 --> 11:23.682
HOW VALUABLE IT WAS

11:23.724 --> 11:25.560
-TO JUST TAKE TIME TO PLAY.

11:23.724 --> 11:25.560
-PLAY.

11:25.602 --> 11:27.521
YEAH, HE -- HE REMINDED ME

11:25.602 --> 11:27.521
OF THAT ALL THE TIME.

11:27.562 --> 11:28.855
